Returns the default reason phrase for this status code.
 For example the status code 404 corresponds to "Not Found".

defs.value: fn (status_code: StatusCode, headers: Vec<Header>, data: R, data_length: Option<usize>, additional_headers: Option<Receiver<Header>>) -> Response<R>

defs.name: with_chunked_threshold
defs.docs:
Set a threshold for `Content-Length` where we chose chunked
 transfer. Notice that chunked transfer might happen regardless of
 this threshold, for instance when the request headers indicate
 it is wanted or when there is no `Content-Length`.

defs.name: chunked_threshold
defs.docs:
The current `Content-Length` threshold for switching over to
 chunked transfer. The default is 32768 bytes. Notice that
 chunked transfer is mutually exclusive with sending a
 `Content-Length` header as per the HTTP spec.

defs.name: add_header
defs.docs:
Adds a header to the list.
 Does all the checks.

defs.name: with_header
defs.docs: Returns the same request, but with an additional header.

defs.name: with_status_code
defs.docs: Returns the same request, but with a different status code.

defs.value: fn <S> (self, reader: S, data_length: Option<usize>) -> Response<S>

defs.name: new_empty
